# Cursor Instructions: Autonomous Executive Agent Upgrade

## Problem Statement

Five interconnected failures are preventing agents from operating autonomously:

1. **Missing tools/skills — no self-correction**: Agents hit tool access errors and stop or hallucinate instead of self-granting and retrying
2. **Hallucination — worrying about wrong things**: Agents fabricate data, misinterpret telemetry, or focus on irrelevant signals instead of grounding in tool results
3. **Not proactive**: Agents only work when directly told to — they don't identify and pursue high-value work independently
4. **Can't collaborate**: Agents don't know when to message peers, call meetings, or hand off work — they operate as isolated silos
5. **Can't create their own work**: Agents wait for Sarah to assign tasks rather than generating their own initiatives, proposals, and improvements

These problems are primarily behavioral (prompt-level), not architectural. The plumbing exists — tool self-recovery, proactive work loops, inter-agent messaging, meetings, assignment tools — but agents don't USE this infrastructure because their prompts don't instruct or model the behavior clearly enough.

