// Description: Propose a new initiative to Sarah Chen for evaluation. 
//   Sarah will determine if it warrants a founder directive or can be 
//   handled as a standing task. Include: title, business justification 
//   (why now, what's the cost of inaction), proposed assignments 
//   (which agents, what tasks), expected outcome, and estimated effort.
//
// Parameters:
//   title: string — initiative name
//   justification: string — why this matters, what data supports it
//   proposed_assignments: Array<{agent_role, task_description}> — suggested work breakdown
//   expected_outcome: string — what success looks like
//   priority: 'critical' | 'high' | 'medium' | 'low'
//   estimated_days: number
//
// Behavior:
//   → INSERT into a new `proposed_initiatives` table
//   → send_agent_message to chief-of-staff with the proposal
//   → Sarah evaluates and either creates a directive or responds with feedback
```

#### 5b. Add initiative evaluation to Sarah's orchestration cycle

**File:** `packages/agents/src/chief-of-staff/systemPrompt.ts`

In the ORCHESTRATION_PROMPT, add a new responsibility:

