## Key Principle

The architecture is already built for autonomy. The agents have tools for self-recovery, collaboration, proactive work, and work creation. What's missing is the behavioral firmware — the prompt-level instructions that model WHEN and HOW to use these capabilities. Every fix above is fundamentally a prompt improvement backed by small runtime changes to make the happy path automatic.

The single most impactful change: **Fix 1b (auto-grant read-only tools)**. This eliminates the #1 source of stalls and hallucinations — agents spinning on tool access they could trivially have.

The single most transformative change: **Fix 5a-5c (propose_initiative)**. This turns agents from passive executors into active partners who identify problems and propose solutions.